  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study will compare efficacy of versabase gel with 20% sarracenia purpurea versus placebo
      applied every 3-4 hours to herpes lesions.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Patients screened for hsv one or two. Patients with herpes given a 1/8 oz of gel. Researcher
      does not know which is active and which is placebo (placebo is actually just versabase gel).
      Patent applies gel to lesions every 3-4 hours. Returns to clinic on days 3, 5, and 14 for
      evaluation. Up to 50 patients may be enrolled.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
